    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "sitting in the quiet just makes it worse, though. it's not peaceful, it's just hollow. i look at his side of the bed and i just feel like i'm waiting for a life that isn't coming back. it feels so stupid to even keep trying to do the dishes or go to work or pretend like there's a future. what's the point of holding onto a reality that's just broken?",
